title: March Debuts: Not Reading not an option, by gesserit's reckoning
description:
"Not Reading Debuts" ( <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/tag/Not+Reading+Debuts" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/tag/Not+Reading+Debuts</a>  ) are part of the http://thepiratebay.se/tag/Not+Reading project, and contain all first issues published and/or released during a given month that made an uploader's personal cut.

The month being March 2014 and the uploader being me in this case, obviously.

This instalment contains:

   Headspace   #1        - Monkeybrain Comics - Alternate Reality / Crime / Mystery

   The Revenge #1        - Image Comics       - Crime / Metafiction / Pulp

   Starlight   #1        - Image Comics       - Romance / Sci-Fi / Superhero

   Veil        #1        - Dark Horse Comics  - Crime / Mystery / Sci-Fi

   The Witcher #1 (of 5) - Dark Horse Comics  - Adventure / Fantasy / Supernatural

Notes:

 - "Headspace" and "Veil", I was sold on pretty much from the first page.

 - "Witcher" went from "a bit trite" to "a bit jumbled" to "intriguing", to my mind.

 - "Revenge" isn't really my kind of comic on the face of it, but does have a few
   promising elements, and is an Image title, so it gets the benefit of the doubt.

 - "Starlight" seems entirely generic and dull so far, and does not have any
   obviously promising elements either, but it's Millar and Image, so ditto.
